# Public Assets Directory

Place your images, favicon, and other static assets in this directory.

## Required Assets for Production

### Favicon and Icons
- `favicon.ico` - 32x32 favicon
- `icon-192x192.png` - 192x192 PWA icon
- `icon-512x512.png` - 512x512 PWA icon

### Social Media Images  
- `og-image.png` - 1200x630 Open Graph image for social sharing
- `twitter-image.png` - 1200x630 Twitter Card image (optional, can use og-image)

### Profile and Project Images
- Profile photos for about page
- Project screenshots for portfolio
- Research paper figures or diagrams
- Blog post images

## Image Optimization Tips

- Use WebP format when possible for better compression
- Optimize images before uploading (recommended tools: TinyPNG, ImageOptim)
- Next.js Image component provides automatic optimization
- Keep file sizes reasonable for web performance

## Directory Structure Example

```
public/
├── favicon.ico
├── icon-192x192.png
├── icon-512x512.png
├── og-image.png
├── profile/
│   ├── headshot.jpg
│   └── about-photo.jpg
├── projects/
│   ├── spaced-repetition-app.png
│   └── research-tool.png
└── blog/
    ├── post-1-image.jpg
    └── post-2-diagram.png
```